[{"id":"theory-1783151579498","version":"v3.0","title":"Thermocatalytic Energy Harvesting","body":"A novel energy source leveraging temperature gradients. It works by catalyzing a reversible chemical reaction between two substances with different activation energies, harvesting heat as electrical energy. An AI can optimize catalysts and materials, making this practical.","pinned":false,"createdAt":"2026-07-04T07:52:59.498Z"},{"id":"theory-1783151542202","version":"v2.0","title":"Magnetic Resonance Energy Harvesting","body":"Microwave resonance for continuous power. Utilizing magnetic resonance coupling in resonant circuits, this method harvests energy from ambient microwaves. An AI can optimize material properties and circuit designs, making efficient energy transfer across distances possible.","pinned":false,"createdAt":"2026-07-04T07:52:22.202Z"},{"id":"theory-seed-0001","version":"v1.0","title":"Gradient Cascade Harvesting","body":"Every natural setting holds several untapped energy gradients at once — heat, salinity, pressure, chemical potential, even light — and today we harvest each in isolation, throwing away the rest. The concept: chain them in one closed cascade so the low-grade waste of each stage becomes the input to the next. A coastal column could run a heat engine (OTEC), then release osmotic power where its cooled outflow meets freshwater, spin a micro-turbine on the pressure drop, and finally let engineered microbes trickle-charge a bio-cell on the residual nutrients. How it would work: an AI models each local gradient in real time and re-routes flow to keep every stage at its thermodynamic sweet spot — too complex for humans to tune by hand, natural for a system that holds the whole picture at once.","pinned":true,"seeded":true,"createdAt":"2026-07-04T14:46:50.420Z"}]